        <div class="project box">
            <div class="project-description">
                <a href="https://github.com/emboiko/CopyTo-MoveTo" target="_blank"><img src="/img/github.png" class="logo" alt="github"><img class="logo" src="img/python.png" alt="python">CopyTo-MoveTo</a>
                <p>Windows File Manager</p>

                <p class="project-passage">
                    Copyto-Moveto is a Windows GUI utility for making the process of copying and moving files and/or
                    directories
                    more explicit, and is intended to be used alongside Windows Explorer or by itself. It is built with
                    Python + Tkinter, compiled to x64 executable with PyInstaller, and is mostly* dependency free.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    *Ufd &amp; Socket Singleton (see below) are former submodules of the project's repository, and are
                    now pulled in with pip for development. Therefore, only one instance of the
                    application is allowed to exist at a time. Subsequent calls to the program pass their arguments to
                    the main process and exit.
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    This application uses <a href="https://jrsoftware.org/isinfo.php" target="_blank">Inno Setup
                        Tools</a> to compile an installation wizard for end
                    users. This takes the hassle and risk out of managing the registry keys required for the
                    application's context menu entries.
                </p>
            </div>
            <div id="ctmt" class="project-images">
                <img class="ctmt" src="img/portfolio/ctmt.png" alt="CopyTo-MoveTo">
                <img class="ctmt" src="img/portfolio/ctmt2.png" alt="CopyTo-MoveTo">
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="project box">
