                <a href="https://github.com/emboiko/Ufd" target="_blank"><img src="/img/github.png" class="logo" alt="github"><img class="logo" src="img/python.png" alt="python">Ufd</a>
                <p>Unopinionated/Universal file dialog</p>
                <p class="project-passage">
                    This program was [primarily] created to work around the limitations of built-in filedialogs included
                    in dotNET, Tcl, and other GUI libraries. Standard dialogs do not generally support multi-selection
                    of both
                    files and directories from a single dialog.
                    <br><br>
                    Ufd doesn't care what kind of dialog it's serving as- you get to deal with any ambiguities in your
                    own way. Want to select 3 directories and 2 files
                    from the same dialog, and have their paths returned as a list? No worries. Perhaps you'd prefer to
                    corral the user into selecting a single file instead- simply modify the constructor accordingly.
                    <br><br>
                    Packaged with <a href="https://pypi.org/project/Ufd/" target="_blank">PyPi</a>.
                    <br>
                    <span class="codeblock">pip install Ufd --upgrade</span>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div id="ufd" class="project-images">
